Azure Web Application Firewall (WAF) protects web applications from common exploits such as:

* SQL injection
* Cross-site scripting
* Bot attacks

WAF works with:

* Azure Front Door
* Application Gateway
* CDN

For example, an online banking application can block malicious web requests before reaching the backend.

A real-life use case is protecting payment systems.

Another example is securing healthcare portals.

WAF enhances application-layer security for public-facing apps.
